<P>
   &QL; 
BACTERIA-COLONIES _ Corrosion-causing bacteria, mostly unnamed but
grouped generally by what they eat and secrete, are extraordinarily
wily creatures, scientists have learned in recent years. The
bacteria are members of a category known as biofilms, prolific
microbes that attach tightly to a surface and fashion a slimy film
overhead that scientists say is unbelievably effective in keeping
disinfectants out. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BACTERIA-LAW _ AlliedSignal Inc. sued Tempe more than four years
ago in U.S. District Court in Phoenix and followed up the next year
with a suit against Phoenix. Both cases are far from trial. The
lawsuits do not specify damage amounts, but in claims filed before
going to court, the aerospace company demanded $4.5 million from
Tempe and $20.75 million from Phoenix to pay for replacement of
fire-sprinkler systems in all its facilities. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL;
