A6845 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r a BC-PERSONALS25-PERSONALS     10-24 0782
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PERSONALS25-PERSONALS-NYTIMES </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   By LEAH GARCHIK &QC; 
COPYRIGHT 1999 San Francisco Chronicle
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FREEDOM OF CONVERSATION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A delegation of writers _ including  &UR; Judy Blume &LR; , &UR; Chang-rae &LR; 
 &UR; Lee &LR;  and  &UR; Herbert Gold &LR;  _ in Washington last week for the PEN
/Faulkner Awards paid a call on Supreme Court Justice  &UR; Clarence &LR; 
 &UR; Thomas &LR; . Two members of the delegation,  &UR; Calvin Trillin &LR;  and
 &UR; Edward Albee &LR; , had bowed out because the invitation had suggested
that ``confrontational questions'' would be inappropriate.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't want to make a big deal out of this,'' said Trillin.
``I just didn't want to go.'' He said his decision wasn't political
but that he didn't like restrictions being placed on his
conversation. Playwright Albee said he didn't want to honor Thomas
with his presence.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas had turned down invitations in previous years, and agreed
only after being informed that he would be the only justice to have
refused meeting with a PEN/Faulkner delegation. Washington Post
reporters were barred; an attempt to keep out any writers who
considered themselves journalists fell apart when more than half
raised their hands when they were asked. They all said they
wouldn't write about the meeting, though.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas told the writers that he doesn't read novels and reads
only one part of only one newspaper: the sports section of the New
York Post. ``He said, `My opinions really don't matter because I
just follow the law, so it doesn't make any difference what my
opinions are,''' said Gold.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HEROES AND OTHERS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Benson Ford Jr. &LR; , great-grandson of anti-Semitic auto tycoon
 &UR; Henry Ford &LR; , has bought a 500-year-old Torah written in secret in
</P>
<P>
   Spain or Portugal and donated it to a Jewish congregation near
Detroit. The restoration of the Torah was a gift to his wife,
 &UR; Frances &LR; , to whom he was married on July 11 by Rabbi  &UR; Daniel &LR; 
 &UR; Schwartz  &LR; of that congregation.
</P>
<P>
   - The Indiana Department of Natural Resources says it will cite
University of Indiana basketball coach  &UR; Bobby Knight  &LR; for not
reporting his accidental shooting of a hunting companion earlier
this month. DNR warden  &UR; Gerald Carow &LR;  said Knight is ``feeling
bad'' about the accident.
</P>
<P>
   - Dinah's Garden Hotel in Palo Alto is about to unveil an &UR; FDR &LR; 
Memorial Suite, with at least one fitting tribute to the disabled
president: a steam room with wheelchair access.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Howard Stern  &LR; and his wife,  &UR; Alison &LR; , have separated after 21
years of marriage. Spokesman  &UR; Dan Klores  &LR; said the separation ``is
amicable,'' a phrase Stern would probably poke fun at if he were
describing someone else's situation. The Sterns, both 45, have
three daughters, 16, 12 and 6.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Elton John &LR;  and  &UR; B.B. King &LR;  performed at the wedding in
Australia this weekend of  &UR; James Packer &LR; , 32-year-old heir to a
media fortune, and model  &UR; Jodie Meares &LR; . John's fee was estimated
at $800,000; the total wedding bill was said be $10 million.
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Byron Schiffman  &LR; and  &UR; Alison Owings  &LR; were intrigued by the
description, in a recent newspaper notice, of Gordon-Biersch's
Oktoberfest parties, where the staff would be wearing
``leiderhosen,'' which means ``unfortunate pants.'' Too bad they're
not ``liederhosen,'' writes Owings, which would have been ``singing
pants.'' Lederhosen, leather pants, are traditional for the
occasion.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOME TEAM WINNERS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Since we don't have a long hot summer,  &UR; Wendy Nankeville &LR;  admits
that naming a dish from San Francisco the Long Hot Summertime Salad
was a bit sneaky, but never mind, it worked. ``The Long Hot
Summer'' was the first movie in which  &UR; Joanne Woodward  &LR; and  &UR; Paul &LR; 
 &UR; Newman &LR;  co-starred, and Nankeville, office manager at the San
Francisco Food Bank, won $10,000 for that organization in a
Newman's Own/Good Housekeeping recipe contest in New York last
week.
</P>
<P>
   And singing sisters  &UR; Kelly &LR;  and  &UR; Kamille Rudisill &LR;  of the School
of the Arts High School were chosen New Stars of the Week on Pax
TV's ``Destination Stardom'' on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   And  &UR; Jonathan &LR;  and  &UR; Hillary Reinis &LR; , producers of Dame Edna
Everage's ``The Royal Tour,'' are exulting in New York reviews of
the show _ ``Sit back and let the magnificent Dame take charge,''
wrote  &UR; Vincent Canby  &LR; of the New York Times _ which opened there
last week.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm into it in terms of the psychology and drama, as an
entertainment, but politically I think it's absurd _ a vicious
embarrassment between two people who couldn't deserve each other
more.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  -  &LR; Actor and comedian &UR; Richard Belzer &LR;  on a possible New York
senatorial race between &UR; Hillary Clinton &LR;  and &UR; Rudolph Giuliani &LR; ,
quoted in the Washington Post.
