<HEADER>
A6904 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT &LR;      10-24 0394
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CREDIT OFFERINGS SCHEDULED FOR THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used once instead of
the symbol, which is non-transmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Monday's regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills and
an auction of two-year notes on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.91
percent, and a six-month bill was 5.04 percent. In when-issued
trading the two-year note was offered at a price to yield 5.90
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   China Telecom, $500 million of 5-year global bonds,
Baa2/BBB/---. Chase Securities, Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co. and Bank of
China International.
</P>
<P>
   Southern Union Co., $300 million due in 2029,
Baa2/BBB(PLUS)/---. Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette and Merrill Lynch
&AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM Corporatewatch
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Moody's Investors Service/Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp./Duff
&AMP; Phelps Credit.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY
</P>
<P>
   King County, Wash, $60 million of revenue bonds. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY
</P>
<P>
   Wisconsin, $100 million of general obligation bonds.
Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Arizona Department of Transit, $151.6 million of debt
securities. Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Municipal Authority of Anchorage, $75 million of Alaska water
and sewer revenue bonds. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Nebraska Investment Finance Authority, $70 million of debt
securities. Lehman Brothers.
</P>
<P>
   New Mexico State Highway Commission, $100 million of senior
subordinate lien tax revenue highway bonds. Dain Rauscher Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Piedmont Triad Airport Authority, North Carolina, $52 million of
debt securities. The Robinson-Humphrey Co.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa, Fla., $65 million of cigarette-tax revenue bonds for Lee
Muffet. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Texas Department of Housing and Community Affairs, $142.5
million of residential mortgage revenue bonds. M.R. Beal &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Wichita, Kan., Hospital Facility, $105 million of improvement
bonds for Via Cristy Health Systems. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
