<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-24 23:09 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7125 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-SOC-GALAXY-RAPIDS-LAD     10-24 0538
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXY-RAPIDS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GALAXY CAPS SWEEP OF RAPIDS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ Danny Pena was one of the first Los Angeles Galaxy
players showered and clothed following the Galaxy's 2-0 victory
over Colorado on Sunday at Mile High Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   As soon as he sat down and looked over his shoulder, he could
see the small group of reporters coming his way. For Pena, the
well-deserved attention is something he's coming to expect,
especially this time of year. And the way he wears his emotions on
the field is the same way he fires back answers to questions.
</P>
<P>
   After spending most of the afternoon containing Swedish
midfielder Anders Limpar _ the Galaxy's man-mark specialist ended a
scoreless affair in the 74th minute, beating Rapids goalkeeper Ian
Feuer _ which proved to be the knockout blow as Los Angeles swept
Colorado, 2-0, in the best-of-three first-round series to reach the
Western Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
   Now the Galaxy awaits the outcome of Wednesday's Chicago-Dallas
match. Chicago beat Dallas 4-0 Saturday to extend their series to a
deciding game. The winner will face the Galaxy on Sunday at the
Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   With the goal, Pena, believe it or not, became the Galaxy's
all-time leading scorer in the playoffs, raising his total to four
after hammering home three last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``The referee Rich Grady said, `Why do you always wait for the
playoffs to score goals?' said Pena. ``I just smiled. I didn't feel
I gave my team what it needed offensively for a good 80 minutes,
but it only takes one good moment to rectify that.''
</P>
<P>
   The goal, set up brilliantly by playmaker Mauricio Cienfuegos,
caught the Rapids by surprise. Cienfuegos was dribbling to his
right, drifting away from the Rapids net, then dumped a no-look
pass the other direction for Pena, who was alone inside the penalty
area. When Feuer came out to challenge, Pena's delicate chip found
the center of the net.
</P>
<P>
   ``Cien is always telling me not to talk to him, that he will
find me,'' Pena said. ``I never said a word to him, and, sure
enough, he found me like the magic player that he is and I was
fortunate enough to finish it.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was the greatest feeling on earth. It kind of justified
everything that I've gone through over the course of the last three
years. You're looking at a happy man right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Schmid said he felt Pena would do something special when he
walked off the bus.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was the one guy walking around who definitely had his game
face on,'' Schmid said. ``Danny Pena, you can never take this away
from him, he will give you everything he has till he takes his last
breath on the field. He wants to win at all costs and it was a
much-deserved goal for him.''
</P>
<P>
   Galaxy substitute Joey Franchino finished a rebound in the 84th
minute to seal the victory _ but most of the Galaxy's best work
came in the first 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Limpar, who said in the Denver papers that Colorado would come
out and attack, was true to his word. Galaxy goalkeeper Kevin
Hartman needed to make three big saves early and the rest of Los
Angeles' defense weathered the storm until the Galaxy found its
rhythm offensively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
